Abdomen yellowish brown. Tergum 
9 in
dorsal view with an arcuate anterior incision, a nearly U-shaped posterior incision, and an elongate dorsoprocessus, leaving a pair of broad hemitergites, which are obtuse distally and densely haired, dorsoprocessus rectangular, slightly narrowed medially, widened and slightly convex on posterior margin (
Fig. 36
). Sternum 9 shorter than tergum 9, arcuately convex posteriad and bearing long setae in ventral view. Ectoproct in dorsal view subtrapezoidal, posterodorsally with a pair of feebly tubercle-shaped projections, posteroventrally with a pair of curved bifid unguiform projections (visible in dorsal view) (
Fig. 36
) and a short feebly sclerotized digitiform processus (visible in caudal view) (
Fig. 39
). Gonocoxite 9 (
Fig. 37
) in ventral view slightly shorter than gonocoxite 10, distally with an acutely pointed apex. Gonocoxite 
10 in
ventral view with acutely pointed apex and spinous subdistal projection. Gonocoxite 11 forming an arcuate sclerite, connecting to bases of gonocoxites 9 and 10. Hypandrium internum subtrapezoidal.
